  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In addition to the core risk categories, we included a top-tier category, called Other, which annotators selected when no predefined category applied under the given policy.",
    "For instances labeled as Other, annotators were asked to choose from a set of potentially unsafe categories not yet included in the taxonomy or to provide a free-text description of the most relevant hazard, along with an explanation.",
    "As demonstrated by Zhang et al. (2023), free-text explanations significantly improve the identification of subtle unsafe content.",
    "This approach facilitates risk discovery, enhances scalability, and supports policy updates.",
    "We later integrate these free-text annotations into the fine-grained categories outlined in Table 2."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "As demonstrated by Zhang et al. (2023), free-text explanations significantly improve the identification of subtle unsafe content."
  ]
}